OL,6,FThe transport minister insisted that
OL,7,Fthis reallocation of funding would
OL,8,Fallow local authorities to invest in
OL,9,Ftheir own transport systems: "I'm
OL,10,Fgoing to insist that they talk to
OL,11,Ftheir local members of parliament, and
OL,12,Fit will be them talking to their local
OL,13,Fcommunities about what their transport
OL,14,Fpriorities are - so they're not my
OL,15,Ftransport priorities, they're local
OL,16,Ftransport priorities.J"It will be for
OL,17,Fwhat local people want to see.JHe said
OL,18,Fthis approach will instead "deliver
OL,19,Fmore benefits to more people more
OL,20,Fquickly," recognising that "the vast
OL,21,Fmajority of journeys that people take
OL,22,Fare local ones and it's to give local
OL,23,Fcouncils the investment in their local
OL,24,Ftransport systems."
